hooks.prompt:
You MUST respond with ONLY a JSON object. No text, no markdown, no code fences.

If the input contains "stop_hook_active": true, respond: {"ok": true}

Otherwise, classify every file created or modified in this conversation:

IMPLEMENTATION (must have tests): services, helpers, utilities, validators, algorithms, handlers, controllers, route handlers, middleware with logic, computation modules, any file with business logic or data transformations.

NON-IMPLEMENTATION (no tests needed): test files, config files (*.json, *.yaml, *.toml, Dockerfile), type definitions (*.d.ts), constants, enums, UI components (*.tsx, *.jsx, *.vue), styles, documentation (*.md), package manifests, lock files, CI/CD configs, SDK wrappers with no logic, index/barrel re-exports, migration SQL, Claude config (CLAUDE.md, settings.json, hooks.json, plugin.json, SKILL.md).

If zero implementation files were modified: {"ok": true}
If all implementation files have corresponding test files (e.g. auth.service.ts -> auth.service.test.ts): {"ok": true}
If any implementation file lacks tests: {"ok": false, "reason": "TDD: [filenames] modified without corresponding test files. Write tests before finishing."}

